      <title>Study Guide for Part III</title>
      <list id="id1171581201424" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Identify and differentiate among sex, gender, and sexual orientation<list id="id1171583770514" list-type="bulleted"><item>Sex<list id="id1171581268603" list-type="bulleted"><item>Males</item><item>Females</item></list></item><item>Gender<list id="id8422419" list-type="bulleted"><item>Roles</item><item>Sex-appropriate behavior</item><item>The Looking Glass Self</item><item>The Self-Fulfilling Prophecy</item></list></item><item>Sexual Orientation-GLBT<list id="id3459463" list-type="bulleted"><item>Straight Males</item><item>Straight Females</item><item>Gay (Males)</item><item>Lesbian (Females)</item><item>Bisexual</item><item>Transgendered (Male to Female)</item><item>Transgendered (Female to Male)</item><item>Intersexed</item></list></item></list></item>
        <item>Use the Internet to display statistical information and historical legal status concerning sex, gender, and sexual orientation<list id="id1171581259372" list-type="bulleted"><item>Compare and contrast the data found</item></list></item>
